- Picker filter contract: the match-picker modal (`#match-picker-modal`) carries facets — duration band, player count, submitter, full-roster Players (with Match-mode `any of these` / `all of these` and Role `any` / `Commander` / `Thug`). State is `pickerState` in `js/app.js`, persisted in sessionStorage under `vt.picker.filters.v2` (one-shot v1 migration on first read). The All Matches card subtitle, the All-Matches view's filter banner, and the trigger subtitles all update from `applyPickerFilters()`; when the user is on the All Matches view, a debounced `loadAllMatches()` rerun re-aggregates from cached contributions so the career table / radar / global meta reflect the new subset.
- Sentinel damage reference: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §7 "Sentinel Damage Filter" (full evidence chain + decompile + struct layout for the `DAMAGE_TYPE_UNKNOWN` force-kill pathway; linked from rules + DEVELOPER_GUIDE). UnitDestroyed four-way classification + powerup economy reference: same dictionary §8.
- Team faction detection (ISDF / Hadean / Scion): `detect_team_factions()` in `scripts/process_stats.py` derives each team's faction from per-slot ODF first-letter votes (Algorithm A: starting-ship `PlayerState.odf` per slot; Algorithm B: event-stream votes from every team-attributed vehicle/structure/pilot ODF). Output at `match.team_factions = {"1": {"code", "name"} | null, "2": ...}`, sibling to `team_leaders`. Match-global, always-unfiltered. Bumped `match.schema_version` from 2 to 3. Faction badges render via `.vt-faction-badge[data-faction-code]` in `css/vtstats-theme.css` next to team-leader names in `renderFactionScoreboard()`. Full per-source vote table + edge cases: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §9.
- Match winner inference: `compute_match_winner(kill_feed)` in `scripts/process_stats.py` derives `match.winner` from the cleaned kill feed via a toggle model on recycler/factory destructions. Outcomes are `clean_win` (one team fully dead, other untouched) / `contested` (both fully dead, tie-broken by fall order) / `unclear` (rebuild ambiguity, host quit, timeout, commander self-demo). Always emitted; `team` / `loser` are `null` for unclear. Renderer (`renderKillFeed()` in `js/app.js`) injects a `.vt-winner-badge[data-decided-by]` in the Kill Feed card header (with Bootstrap tooltip on contested/unclear), highlights the winning team's `.vt-faction-panel` with `.vt-faction-panel--winner`, and inserts an in-feed `.vt-killfeed-milestone` divider at `decided_at_tick`. **Filter-safe**: read winner from `currentData.match.winner`, never from the (filterable) `kills.feed`. Full toggle-model rationale + edge cases: `docs/DATA_DICTIONARY.md` §10.
